laboratory_examinations.findings: At birth: Serum adjusted-calcium 2.11 mmol/L (8.44 mg/dL); normal range 2.00 -2.80 mmol/L (8.0 -11.2 mg/dL). At 7 days: Low serum adjusted-calcium 1.57 mmol/L (6.28 mg/dL); elevated phosphate 3.45 mmol/L (10.7 mg/dL); PTH 2.2 pmol/L; normal range 1.0 -9.3 pmol/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: The serum calcium concentration increased into the normal range over 48 hours after treatment.

laboratory_examinations.findings: At 7 days: Elevated serum phosphate 3.45 mmol/L (10.7 mg/dL); normal range 1.30 -2.60 mmol/L (4.0 -8.0 mg/dL).
At 7 days: PTH 2.2 pmol/L; normal range 1.0 -9.3 pmol/L.
At 7 days: Borderline low serum magnesium 0.62 mmol/L (1.5 mg/dL); normal range 0.62 -1.00 mmol/L (1.5-2.4 mg/dL).
At 7 days: Low serum 25-hydroxyvitamin D 27 nmol/L; adequate >50 nmol/L.
Discharged at 3 weeks of age with normal serum calcium.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Serum calcium improved to normal after treatment over 48 hours.
